Problem 1

Description of Dataset

  • The Homocide dataset includes 12 variables: uid, reported_date, victim_last, victim_first, victim_race, victim_age, victim_sex, city, state, lat, lon, disposition.
  • The dataset has 52179 rows and 12 columns.
  • The number of homocides in the dataset is 52179.

Total Homcides

homocide = 
  read_csv(file = "./data/homicide-data.csv", na = c("", "Unknown")) %>%  #changes unknown to NA
  mutate(city_state = str_c(city, state),
         resolution = case_when(
           disposition == "Closed without arrest"     ~ "unsolved",
           disposition == "Open/No arrest"            ~ "unsolved",
           disposition == "Closed by arrest"          ~ "solved")) %>% 
  relocate(city_state) %>% 
  filter(city_state != "TulsaAL")

Proportions of Homocides in Baltimore

baltimore_df = homocide %>% 
  filter(city_state == "BaltimoreMD")

baltimore_summary = baltimore_df %>% 
  summarize(
    unsolved = sum(resolution == "unsolved"),
    n = n())

baltimore_test = prop.test(
  x = baltimore_summary %>% pull(unsolved),
  n = baltimore_summary %>% pull(n))

baltimore_test %>% 
  broom::tidy()

Proportions of Homocides all Cities

prop_test_function = function(city_df) {
  
  city_summary = city_df %>% 
    summarize(
    unsolved = sum(resolution == "unsolved"),
    n = n())

  city_test = prop.test(
    x = city_summary %>% pull(unsolved),
    n = city_summary %>% pull(n))

return(city_test)

}

prop_test_function(baltimore_df)
results_df = homocide %>% 
  nest(data = uid:resolution) %>% 
  mutate(
    test_results = map(data, prop_test_function),
    tidy_results = map(test_results, broom::tidy)) %>% 
  select(city_state, tidy_results) %>% 
  unnest(tidy_results) %>% 
  select(city_state, estimate, starts_with("conf"))

Plot

results_df %>% 
  mutate(city_state = fct_reorder(city_state, estimate)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = city_state, y = estimate)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = conf.low, ymax = conf.high)) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust = 1))

Problem 2

Tidying

dataframe = tibble(files = list.files("data/zip_data/")) %>% 
  mutate(
    path_name = paste0("./data/zip_data/", files),
    data = map(.x = path_name, ~read_csv(.x))) %>% 
  mutate(files = str_replace(files, ".csv", "")) %>% 
  unnest(data) %>% 
  select(-path_name) %>% 
  pivot_longer(
    week_1:week_8,
    names_to = "week",
    values_to = "data") %>% 
  separate(week, into = c("week1", "week"), sep = "_") %>% 
  select(-week1) %>% 
  mutate(week = as.numeric(week)) %>% 
  mutate(group = files) %>% 
  separate(group, into = c("group", "ID"), sep = "_") %>% 
  select(-"ID") %>% 
  mutate(group = ifelse(group == "con", "Experimental", "Control"))

Plot

plot = dataframe %>% 
  group_by(files) %>%  
  ggplot(aes(x = week, y = data, color = group)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .6) + geom_path() +
  labs(
    title = "Data Values over Time in each Experimental Group",
    x = "Week",
    y = "Data value",
    color = "group") + 
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")

library(tidyverse)

set.seed(10)

iris_with_missing = iris %>% 
  map_df(~replace(.x, sample(1:150, 20), NA)) %>%
  mutate(Species = as.character(Species))

Function

fill_in_missing = function(x) {
  
  if (typeof(x) == "character") 
  {x[is.na(x)]="virginica"}
  
  else 
  {x[is.na(x)]= mean(x, na.rm = TRUE) }
  
  return(x)
  
  }

Mapping

output = map(iris_with_missing, fill_in_missing)
